1
00:00:01,010 --> 00:00:02,670
(Episode 34)

2
00:00:02,670 --> 00:00:06,210
I'm asking what you've been doing
with a married man.

3
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:09,050
Who is it?

4
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:12,350
The person who tailed me
and took these awful photos.

5
00:00:13,220 --> 00:00:15,220
Just answer my question!

6
00:00:15,590 --> 00:00:16,820
It's Professor Kang Nam Bong.

7
00:00:17,490 --> 00:00:20,330
He worked with us
on the hotel renewal project,

8
00:00:21,690 --> 00:00:24,630
and he's the father of Chef Kang Jun Ho,
the man Seo Rin has a crush on.

9
00:00:25,230 --> 00:00:28,400
But why are you seeing him?

10
00:00:28,770 --> 00:00:29,770
Father.

11
00:00:30,270 --> 00:00:31,470
I'm truly disappointed.

12
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:34,710
Why would I ever be seeing another man?

13
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:36,570
When I pulled an all-nighter
a few days ago,

14
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:39,910
I was in a meeting with Professor Kang
about the Dream Resort project.

15
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:42,350
His assistant was with us too.

16
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:48,290
I am the head of Dream Hotel.

17
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:51,660
I have to meet with men as part of my job,

18
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:53,630
and sometimes those meetings run late.

19
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:56,230
So why are you suddenly
questioning me like this?

20
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:58,460
Before Yeom San Wol came along,

21
00:00:58,930 --> 00:01:02,370
you never would have misunderstood me
like this.

22
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:06,770
So you're saying you met
Professor Kang for business?

23
00:01:07,110 --> 00:01:11,980
Yes, and I only recently found out
that his son is Chef Kang Jun Ho.

24
00:01:12,310 --> 00:01:15,350
Since Seo Rin was so fond of him,
I wanted to look into his family,

25
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:17,880
so I took the chance to meet with him.

26
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:18,920
And what did you find out?

27
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:21,520
Professor Kang is a man of fine character,

28
00:01:21,950 --> 00:01:24,590
and Chef Kang Jun Ho's mother is a lawyer.

29
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:29,630
He may not come from a rich family,
but he's a good man from a good home.

30
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:33,530
- So in a way, that was a relief.
- What?

31
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:38,500
I realized we shouldn't be so quick
to just oppose Kang Jun Ho.

32
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:39,940
It doesn't matter. The answer is no.

33
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:44,910
Seo Rin is my granddaughter,
and she will inherit the Dream Group.

34
00:01:45,210 --> 00:01:48,010
His family can't provide
the kind of backing our Seo Rin needs.

35
00:01:48,450 --> 00:01:50,280
You know exactly what I mean.

36
00:01:51,050 --> 00:01:52,050
Don't forget that.

37
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:56,190
- Yes, Father.
- And watch how you conduct yourself.

38
00:01:56,990 --> 00:01:58,290
A lot of people are watching.

39
00:01:58,290 --> 00:02:01,390
Don't give them any reason to talk.

40
00:02:01,690 --> 00:02:03,600
Yes, I'll be sure to remember that.

41
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:25,620
Gosh, that hurts.

42
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:28,050
What on earth just happened?

43
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:29,650
You got it wrong, didn't you?

44
00:02:30,890 --> 00:02:32,290
She said it was business.

45
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:33,760
Were we just barking up the wrong tree?

46
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:35,630
Oh, my gosh!

47
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:43,430
Yes?

48
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,840
She's calling for you.

49
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,980
What is it? What do you want?

50
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,210
- Oh, my!
- Mom!

51
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:57,250
You want me to humiliate you
in front of your daughter?

52
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,350
What did I do?
Why must you always hit me?

53
00:03:00,420 --> 00:03:02,020
If you deserve a beating, you get one!

54
00:03:02,690 --> 00:03:05,020
You. Did you have me followed?

55
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:08,660
You're the one who took those photos
and gave them to the Chairman, aren't you?

56
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:10,930
Who told you that?

57
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,530
Did the Chairman tell you that?

58
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:14,030
It wasn't me.

59
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,800
- I swear it wasn't!
- Then was it Jin Hong Ju?

60
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,040
Was it your daughter's doing?

61
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:21,410
No, it wasn't me.

62
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:23,980
If it were your daughter,
this won't end with a single slap.

63
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:27,750
This time, I might transfer her to Africa
instead of India.

64
00:03:28,210 --> 00:03:29,280
And as for you, Yeom San Wol,

65
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:31,750
you'll be thrown out of this house,
of course.

66
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:34,050
How dare you pull such a malicious stunt!

67
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,090
It was me.

68
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,890
I'm sorry. Please forgive me.

69
00:03:44,530 --> 00:03:47,830
My daughter had nothing to do with this,
CEO Chae.

70
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:49,000
Oh, my!

71
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:54,510
You're hitting me in the same spot
that already hurts!

72
00:03:54,970 --> 00:03:57,110
Do you have any idea how much it hurts
to be hit on a bruise?

73
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:59,480
- You want me to hit the other side, then?
- Oh, gosh.

74
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:03,010
Since you're the one who caused this mess,
you must accept your punishment.

75
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,250
Starting tomorrow,
you will clean this entire house.

76
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:11,790
But what about the housekeeper?

77
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:14,130
You'll wash all the bedding
and the curtains,

78
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:17,900
vacuum, and scrub the stairs
on your hands and knees.

79
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,960
Don't you dare ask the housekeeper
to do it.

80
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:21,600
I'll be checking up on you.

81
00:04:35,210 --> 00:04:36,210
I...

82
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:39,450
like you, Jang Mi. I mean, I love you.

83
00:05:00,670 --> 00:05:01,940
I'm telling you not to wait for me.

84
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:04,680
I already told you.
I don't do things like fall in love.

85
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,680
So it's pointless for you to wait.

86
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,250
Jang Mi.

87
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:18,820
I know you don't really mean that.

88
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:34,940
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

89
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:36,670
Jang Mi, what are you doing?

90
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:39,180
Thinking about you, Baek Ho...

91
00:05:41,450 --> 00:05:43,850
I'm going crazy. Get a grip, Oh Jang Mi!

92
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:52,120
I was sleeping.

93
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:55,430
What on earth? She wasn't sleeping.

94
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,360
How can you text if you're asleep?

95
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:09,310
- What is it?
- What are you doing tomorrow?

96
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,480
Delivering lunch boxes.
What do you think I'd be doing?

97
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:14,380
So you don't have
any other plans tomorrow, right?

98
00:06:14,450 --> 00:06:17,750
I made myself clear.
I'm not going to date you, Lawyer Kang.

99
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:19,050
Okay, that's enough of that.

100
00:06:19,350 --> 00:06:20,820
It's late. Get some sleep.

101
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:22,350
Wait, I was the one trying to sleep...

102
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:24,420
when you called and woke me up.

103
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:25,760
Right. Sorry.

104
00:06:27,230 --> 00:06:28,690
Sleep well. And...

105
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:32,400
- see you tomorrow.
- What do you mean, "see you?"

106
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,070
For a delivery.
I'm going to order a lunch box.

107
00:06:35,130 --> 00:06:36,670
Tae Pyung will be the one
making the delivery.

108
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:39,340
Hello? Hello...

109
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:05,800
What's wrong? You got a toothache?

110
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,130
No, it's not that.

111
00:07:11,070 --> 00:07:13,170
I must have slept on it funny.
It just hurts a little.

112
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:15,270
Here, let me see.

113
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:18,040
- Oh, my. It looks a little swollen.
- Mrs. Yang.

114
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:21,080
From now on, Yeom San Wol
will be doing the cleaning and laundry.

115
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:23,820
So you are not to help her at all.

116
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:25,380
Yes, ma'am.

117
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:28,690
Chairman.

118
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,060
What's all this about?

119
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:35,830
She snooped around, digging for dirt
and making ridiculous accusations,

120
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,000
so she deserves
to be punished accordingly.

121
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,530
If I'm easy on her,
she'll think it's okay...

122
00:07:40,670 --> 00:07:42,870
and do it again.

123
00:07:48,340 --> 00:07:50,910
Mrs. Yang, where did you get this?

124
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,710
You didn't make this, did you?

125
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:57,050
Oh, that. Team Leader Jin bought it
from a side dish shop yesterday.

126
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:58,880
Team Leader Jin did?

127
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,520
- That's a surprise.
- Well...

128
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,350
That?

129
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:05,990
I'm so full.

130
00:08:06,690 --> 00:08:10,290
Mom, where did you get this?
This is incredible.

131
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:12,730
That's right.

132
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:17,500
You know that lunch box from your office?
This is from the same place.

133
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:21,540
Oh, my. CEO Chae,
you order from there as well?

134
00:08:24,380 --> 00:08:27,350
Jin Hong Ju.
How did you know about this place?

135
00:08:27,910 --> 00:08:28,910
Oh, you know.

136
00:08:29,210 --> 00:08:31,450
I just heard the food was good,
so I thought I'd give it a try.

137
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:35,620
Jin Hong Ju went to Oh Jang Mi's shop
and bought this?

138
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:38,490
Does that mean
she might have seen Oh Jang Mi?

139
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:47,000
Manager Lee, we have a huge problem.

140
00:08:47,770 --> 00:08:50,130
- What is it, CEO Chae?
- Find something out for me. It's urgent.

141
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,240
I think Jin Hong Ju may have gone
to Oh Jang Mi's shop.

142
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:57,140
- Team Leader Jin went to see Oh Jang Mi?
- That's right.

143
00:08:57,680 --> 00:09:00,540
Find out why on earth she went there.
Right now.

144
00:09:01,210 --> 00:09:02,210
Right away.

145
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,550
And now Jin Hong Ju too.

146
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:09,920
I can't take this.

147
00:09:15,430 --> 00:09:16,430
Welcome.

148
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,100
I mean, seriously.

149
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:25,040
What does Baek Ho even see in that woman
to have completely lost his mind?

150
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:28,170
That's it.

151
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:31,610
He's clearly fallen under the spell
of her cooking.

152
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:36,610
Otherwise, none of this makes any sense.

153
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:38,880
No, wait.

154
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,550
You know what?
This is actually for the best.

155
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:42,720
If it's her,

156
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:45,160
it'll be a piece of cake
to steal Baek Ho away.

157
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,710
You finished already?

158
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:04,340
- Yes.
- Sit with me for a bit.

159
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,550
- Why?
- Jun Ho went to the early morning market,

160
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:11,820
and Baek Ho ran off, completely smitten
with some girl named Jang Mi.

161
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:15,450
I don't want to eat by myself,
so can't you keep me company?

162
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,320
All right.

163
00:10:18,460 --> 00:10:19,890
Okay, fine. I will.

164
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:22,830
- Here, try some of this fish.
- Okay.

165
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,560
You should have some more too.

166
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,300
Okay. It's delicious.

167
00:10:27,630 --> 00:10:29,370
After hearing what you said,

168
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:32,200
it sounds like your wife
is a wonderful person.

169
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,510
So I don't think it's right
for us to keep meeting like this.

170
00:10:38,310 --> 00:10:40,040
What's wrong? Is something on your mind?

171
00:10:48,790 --> 00:10:50,550
It's about Baek Ho.

172
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:54,530
Why don't you meet this woman he's seeing?

173
00:10:54,830 --> 00:10:55,860
I was already planning to.

174
00:10:57,330 --> 00:11:00,870
A woman who runs a side dish shop?
I have no idea what he sees in her.

175
00:11:04,970 --> 00:11:06,140
I understand.

176
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:11,280
So they sent the DNA test results
by courier.

177
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:25,160
(Courier Service)

178
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:36,730
(Genos Gene Examination Center)

179
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,910
(Genetic Analysis Report)

180
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,610
(Maternal Lineage Test Report)

181
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:54,120
(DNA Test Result Report)

182
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:56,290
(Specimens: Chae Hwa Young, Kang Jun Ho)

183
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:00,660
(DNA Comparison Test Results)

184
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:03,860
(Match)

185
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,200
(Explanation of Test Results
Theory of DNA Match Testing)

186
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:09,270
(Explanation of Results)

187
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:10,730
(The probability of a maternal
relationship is 99.997 percent.)

188
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,340
(Biological relationship confirmed:
Chae Hwa Young and Kang Jun Ho)

189
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:19,580
Jun Ho.

190
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:22,610
So you really are my Ha Neul.

191
00:12:24,450 --> 00:12:25,680
Jun Ho. My son...

192
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:28,990
You're testing my patience,
you arrogant punk!

193
00:12:29,050 --> 00:12:30,320
Let go of me.

194
00:12:31,690 --> 00:12:33,760
My son was this close all along,

195
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:36,030
and I had no idea as his mother.

196
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:38,100
To think that I hit him
with my own hands...

197
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:43,370
What have I done? I'm so sorry, Jun Ho.

198
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,000
I'm so sorry.

199
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:53,310
What right do I have
to ever appear before you again?

200
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:09,160
I hope I'm not intruding.

201
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:13,830
No.

202
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:20,840
I'm here with some documents
that need your signature.

203
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:24,680
I did knock.

204
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:27,780
My son.

205
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:29,910
My amazing son.

206
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:31,950
Jun Ho.

207
00:13:32,650 --> 00:13:36,290
I'm going to make up for everything
I failed to do for you.

208
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,690
CEO Chae, are you feeling unwell?

209
00:13:47,130 --> 00:13:48,300
Just leave them and go.

210
00:13:50,730 --> 00:13:51,740
Very well.

211
00:13:52,070 --> 00:13:54,070
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

212
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:04,080
I'm sorry, Jun Ho.

213
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,150
I'm so sorry, Jun Ho, my son.

214
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:08,690
You were right beside me,
and I didn't even recognize you.

215
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:12,360
What kind of mother
doesn't even recognize her own son's face?

216
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:38,220
I want to get on my knees
and beg for your forgiveness, Jun Ho.

217
00:14:39,820 --> 00:14:42,820
But if I reveal myself now,
I'll only end up hurting you.

218
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:47,590
I have no right to call myself
your mother,

219
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:51,200
but I'm going to give you Dream.

220
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,730
I'll have you marry Seo Rin,

221
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:56,500
and I'll make sure
Dream Group becomes yours.

222
00:14:57,570 --> 00:14:59,440
Seo Rin isn't even my own flesh and blood,
after all.

223
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:02,770
I'm so sorry, my son.

224
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,100
What was that?

225
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:29,600
Why was Hwa Young looking at
Kang Jun Ho like that?

226
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,870
You ordered lunch boxes,
so what's with the dance game?

227
00:15:37,170 --> 00:15:38,940
I'm really not in the mood for this.

228
00:15:39,140 --> 00:15:40,840
Stop whining and just give it a try.

229
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:42,650
You need to blow off some steam, Jang Mi.

230
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:44,280
Stress?

231
00:15:44,950 --> 00:15:46,350
I don't do stress.

232
00:16:35,330 --> 00:16:38,440
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

233
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,210
Welcome.

234
00:16:48,610 --> 00:16:49,950
Feel free to look at our side dishes.

235
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:51,550
Excuse me.

236
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:55,120
- Is Ms. Oh Jang Mi here?
- Jang Mi?

237
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,950
She's not here right now.

238
00:16:58,190 --> 00:16:59,690
May I ask who you are?

239
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:02,690
You probably don't know me,

240
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:04,530
but my son is Kang Baek Ho.

241
00:17:05,530 --> 00:17:06,900
You're Lawyer Kang's mother?

242
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:08,800
It's so nice to meet you.

243
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:10,830
Hi.

244
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:15,070
Jang Mi's gone!
Where did she go? Jang Mi's gone!

245
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:18,210
Suk Hee, where are you going?
Jang Mi will be right back, all right?

246
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:21,040
Jang Mi's gone.
Suk Hee's daughter, Jang Mi, is gone.

247
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:24,380
- I have to go find her.
- Suk Hee.

248
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:25,880
- Dad.
- Yes?

249
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:27,120
That's Lawyer Kang's mother.

250
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,650
Hello.

251
00:17:28,650 --> 00:17:32,060
We're so grateful for all the help
Lawyer Kang has given Jang Mi.

252
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:34,860
- Please come in.
- Jang Mi's gone.

253
00:17:34,860 --> 00:17:35,990
Where did Jang Mi go?

254
00:17:36,060 --> 00:17:39,500
- I have to go find her!
- Suk Hee, Jang Mi will be right back.

255
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,630
Why don't you go get some ice cream
with Tae Pyung, okay?

256
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,030
Tae Pyung!

257
00:17:47,270 --> 00:17:49,140
I'm sorry, our shop is a bit of a mess.

258
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:52,140
Not at all.

259
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:59,520
I'm not sure if it's to your taste.

260
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:03,650
Please have some.

261
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:09,590
Look, I know you must be busy,

262
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:11,460
so I'll get right to the point.

263
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,930
Yes, please do.

264
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,630
Baek Ho is such a good-hearted kid.

265
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:21,370
Even as a lawyer, he does pro bono work
for people who are struggling.

266
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:23,810
He's just so full of compassion.

267
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:28,480
He can't just walk away
from someone he pities.

268
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:30,510
He's kind to a fault. That's his nature.

269
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:32,580
Yes, I'm well aware of that.

270
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:36,450
That's why he's been such a great help
to our family.

271
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,360
Baek Ho has truly been a lifesaver.

272
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:42,360
He probably sees your daughter
in the same way.

273
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:46,030
- I'm sorry?
- Your daughter is Oh Jang Mi, right?

274
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:49,500
- Yes.
- Baek Ho...

275
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:52,300
isn't interested
in your daughter romantically.

276
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:56,240
He's only keeping her close
out of sheer pity.

277
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,610
So I'm asking you
to please put a stop to it.

278
00:18:59,210 --> 00:19:01,510
That's why I've taken the liberty
of coming here today.

279
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:09,950
Well then, I trust I've made myself clear.

280
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:11,590
I'll be on my way now.

281
00:19:18,230 --> 00:19:19,730
Wait a moment, ma'am.

282
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,340
I believe you're mistaken about something.

283
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,140
My daughter Jang Mi isn't the one
who's interested.

284
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:31,410
It's your son, Baek Ho,
who's been pursuing her.

285
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:33,810
You...

286
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:36,280
still don't seem to understand me.

287
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:38,180
No, I heard you loud and clear.

288
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:42,020
So instead of coming here
to say all that to me,

289
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:46,790
you should be the one
talking some sense into your son.

290
00:19:47,820 --> 00:19:49,130
I won't see you out.

291
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:04,040
I'm just asking you to keep me company
while I eat.

292
00:20:04,410 --> 00:20:06,840
- Why should I?
- What do you mean?

293
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:09,180
I'm asking you to keep me company
out of politeness.

294
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,980
Is this why you ordered the lunch boxes?

295
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:13,650
I knew you wouldn't meet me if I asked.

296
00:20:13,650 --> 00:20:15,120
So I had to use the food as an excuse.

297
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:19,320
Here. There are two,
so I can't eat them by myself.

298
00:20:19,390 --> 00:20:20,460
Please eat with me.

299
00:20:22,260 --> 00:20:24,800
Come on, stop it. Seriously.

300
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:32,340
Come on, you're hungry. Let's just eat.

301
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:36,810
Don't keep doing this.

302
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,080
Just for today, okay?
I'm letting it slide.

303
00:20:39,410 --> 00:20:40,410
Okay.

304
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:44,720
But...

305
00:20:45,820 --> 00:20:46,820
why do you have to be so pretty?

306
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:50,020
What did you just say?

307
00:20:52,890 --> 00:20:53,890
Hold on.

308
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:16,810
Dad, don't be so upset.

309
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:19,550
If I were Lawyer Kang's mom,
I'd probably say the same thing.

310
00:21:19,620 --> 00:21:20,780
She's right, Dad.

311
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:23,190
In the end, kids always get their way.

312
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,920
Even if our Jang Mi marries
into a family like that,

313
00:21:26,490 --> 00:21:30,190
she'll only be happy
if her future mother-in-law welcomes her.

314
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:32,760
That's what's upsetting me.

315
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:36,930
Dad, who lives with their mother-in-law
these days?

316
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:40,140
If she's the same after the wedding,
I'll go over there and make a scene.

317
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,510
You hothead.

318
00:21:45,810 --> 00:21:47,240
- I'm home.
- You're back?

319
00:21:47,310 --> 00:21:49,080
Welcome home. You had a long day.

320
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:52,150
Dad, what's with the rice wine
all of a sudden?

321
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,650
I just felt like having some.
Want a glass?

322
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:58,060
No, I'm okay.

323
00:22:08,570 --> 00:22:11,700
Jang Mi. Get a hold of yourself.

324
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:13,700
Okay?

325
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:24,980
Gosh, my back.

326
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:28,250
I'm not used to this kind of work.
It's killing me.

327
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:30,320
Goodness.

328
00:22:31,150 --> 00:22:32,160
Chae Hwa Young.

329
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:34,830
Just you wait and see.

330
00:22:35,530 --> 00:22:36,830
Someday, I swear...

331
00:22:37,090 --> 00:22:39,530
the day will come when I make you pay
for this humiliation.

332
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:47,700
So, luckily, Jin Hong Ju didn't see
Oh Jang Mi, right?

333
00:22:48,470 --> 00:22:51,640
That's right.
According to my guy watching the store,

334
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:54,080
she just bought some side dishes
from Oh Tae Sook.

335
00:22:54,750 --> 00:22:57,080
Also, Professor Kang Nam Bong's wife
stopped by today.

336
00:22:57,380 --> 00:23:00,150
What? Han Young Ja, the lawyer, too?

337
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:03,220
Since Oh Jang Mi is getting close
to Lawyer Kang Baek Ho,

338
00:23:03,490 --> 00:23:04,820
I think she came to check her out.

339
00:23:05,790 --> 00:23:06,790
Unbelievable.

340
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:10,190
All sorts of people are parading
in and out of that side dish shop.

341
00:23:11,060 --> 00:23:12,200
All right, you can go now.

342
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:14,060
Wait.

343
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:17,670
- Yes?
- At Chang Restaurant...

344
00:23:21,510 --> 00:23:22,770
Never mind. Just go.

345
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:24,940
What's going on?

346
00:23:29,510 --> 00:23:32,220
- Is Kang Jun Ho in trouble again?
- No, it's not that.

347
00:23:33,450 --> 00:23:34,450
Hwa Young.

348
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:37,250
You're hiding something from me,
aren't you?

349
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:42,590
I saw you crying earlier,
looking at Kang Jun Ho tenderly.

350
00:23:43,660 --> 00:23:44,660
What was that about?

351
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,630
There's something I don't know,
isn't there?

352
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:52,270
I'm not keeping secrets from you.
Stop it and go your way.

353
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:57,840
If you ever need my help,
just say the word.

354
00:23:58,710 --> 00:24:01,010
And don't forget I'm always on your side.

355
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:17,630
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

356
00:24:18,430 --> 00:24:19,630
Is this one better?

357
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:22,530
This is too drab.

358
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:48,190
I'm out of time. Seriously.

359
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:09,880
That's it.

360
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:13,080
Since I'm clearly
not in my right mind anyway,

361
00:25:14,220 --> 00:25:17,350
I might as well just ask Baek Ho out.

362
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:26,130
Grandpa. Are my hands nice and refreshing?

363
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:28,500
They feel so nice and refreshing.

364
00:25:28,830 --> 00:25:31,770
Who did our Bo Ra get
these clever hands from?

365
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:35,810
Look. Suk Hee is good at this.

366
00:25:35,810 --> 00:25:37,410
Suk Hee can do it too.

367
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:45,320
Who is that?

368
00:25:45,580 --> 00:25:47,020
Is that really my daughter, Oh Jang Mi?

369
00:25:47,020 --> 00:25:49,190
Gosh, Jang Mi, you look so pretty!

370
00:25:49,650 --> 00:25:51,290
My daughter Jang Mi is so pretty!

371
00:25:51,290 --> 00:25:53,090
Jang Mi, you're my daughter.

372
00:25:53,190 --> 00:25:55,990
Auntie, you look so pretty.
You should dress like this all the time.

373
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:59,230
What? So you're saying
I wasn't pretty before?

374
00:26:01,970 --> 00:26:02,970
I'm heading out.

375
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:37,170
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

376
00:26:43,870 --> 00:26:45,010
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

377
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:47,480
It's me, Jin Hong Ju.
You remember me, don't you?

378
00:26:48,410 --> 00:26:49,410
Oh, yes.

379
00:26:49,910 --> 00:26:51,680
What brings you here?

380
00:26:53,220 --> 00:26:55,050
Baek Ho, can you give me a hand with...

381
00:26:57,150 --> 00:26:58,190
Oh, my.

382
00:26:58,860 --> 00:27:02,230
You came to see my Baek Ho, didn't you?

383
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:03,360
Oh, right.

384
00:27:04,030 --> 00:27:07,360
You must be Lawyer Kang Baek Ho's mother.

385
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:11,170
- Hello, Mother.
- "Mother?"

386
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:13,600
Please try some of this, Mother.

387
00:27:21,710 --> 00:27:23,650
- Oh, really?
- I'm telling you, he did.

388
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,180
My goodness.

389
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:28,120
- I wonder who's here.
- To think of running into you here.

390
00:27:28,650 --> 00:27:33,220
Oh, my, so it's true?
Baek Ho really helped you?

391
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:38,330
I never knew Baek Ho
had such a romantic side.

392
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:43,270
Mother, wasn't our Baek Ho
always a romantic at heart?

393
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:44,500
"Mother?"

394
00:27:44,970 --> 00:27:46,500
"Our Baek Ho?"

395
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:47,970
Who is she?

396
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:51,610
Or maybe he's only romantic with me?

397
00:27:55,950 --> 00:27:56,980
Oh, my.

398
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,800
(The First Man)

399
00:28:20,870 --> 00:28:23,240
I plan to recommend you, Chef Kang Jun Ho,
who is young and competent,

400
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,610
for the General Manager position.

401
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:28,510
- I have a condition.
- A condition?

402
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:30,310
An assailant went after Jang Mi again?

403
00:28:31,010 --> 00:28:34,080
CEO Chae, about Jang Mi studying abroad...

404
00:28:34,150 --> 00:28:35,590
Is there any way you could let her go?

405
00:28:36,250 --> 00:28:39,590
- Goodness!
- Who is this solicitor?

406
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:42,690
Jang Mi. What are you doing here?

407
00:28:48,330 --> 00:28:50,330
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
